quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  15,32,"He (Allah) said, "0 Iblis, what is wrong with you that you did not join those who prostrated?""
  15,33,"He said, "I am not the one to prostrate before a human being whom You have created from a sound-giving clay made of decayed mud.""
  15,34,"He said, 'Then, get out from here for you are an outcast."
  15,35,"And upon you is the curse upto the day of Judgment.""
  15,36,"He said, "0 my Lord, then give me respite upto the day they (the dead) shall be raised.""
  15,37,"He (Allah) said, "Well, you are among those given respite"
  15,38,"till the day of the appointed time.""
  15,39,"He said, "My Lord, since You made me go astray, I swear I shall adorn for them (evils) on the earth and shall lead all of them astray,"
  15,40,"except those of Your servants from among them who are chosen (by You).""
  15,41,"He (Allah) said, 'To Me, it is the straight path."
  15,42,"My servants are such that you have no power over them except those who follow you from the deviators."
  15,43,"And the Jahannam (Hell) is the promised place for them all."
  15,44,"It has seven gates. For each gate there is a group apportioned from them.""
  15,45,"Surely, the God-fearing are in Gardens and streams:"
  15,46,"'Enter here in peace, free of fear.""
  15,47,"And We shall have removed whatever grudge they had in their hearts (making them) brothers, sitting on couches, face to face."
  15,48,"No weariness shall touch them nor will they be expelled from there."
  15,49,"Tell My servants that I am the Most-Forgiving, the Very-Merciful"
  15,50,"and that My punishment is the painful punishment."
  15,51,"And tell them about the guests of Ibrahim."